social_posts.post_text:
TLDR: Shop update coming sometime in May…

The long version: I really haven’t thrown much in the last year. With the birth of my precious son, finding time to work in the studio didn’t seem possible. Now that I’m back at work teaching, I’ve felt inspired to get my hands dirty. I have a small group of motivated students taking a clay independent study with me. I’m teaching them how to set a goal as an artist and make a plan to achieve that goal. To illustrate this process and to practice what I teach, I decided to set my own goal: a shop update in mid-May of new work that speaks to my new role as a mother. First step: playing with new mug forms.

When mending imitates pottery…

My body has changed SO MUCH in the last year. It grew a human, birthed a beautiful baby, and now nourishes him. My body has often felt like his and not my own. My clothes have had to fit my ever expanding curves and be able to whip my boobs out at a moment’s notice. With all this change, I lost my personal fashion. Then I discovered @katrinarodabaugh and her book Mending Matters. I bought a pair of tattered jeans that actually fit from @thefashiongodsfalmouth (8 sizes larger than my last pair!) and mended them by hand. I’m loving the experimentation of color blocking similar to what I do on my pottery.

Hand printed pig patch by @addiebeststudio

Being a full-time mom and a full-time art teacher hasn’t left me much time to make pots, especially when I’ve picked up another hobby: sewing my own clothes! I made this top and I’m really proud of it 🤩 It’s the #collagegathertop by @matchymatchysewingclub, with about 6” added to the length.

I’m working my way towards a small shop update of #nubmugs though! Just wait, maybe I’ll even make another process reel for you…
